Reasoning: 
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity): The paper discusses the complexity of unsatisfiable linear k-CNF formulas and their impact on Davis-Putnam style splitting algorithms, which falls under the scope of computational complexity.
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms): The paper discusses the structure of unsatisfiable linear k-CNF formulas and their impact on resolution refutation, which falls under the scope of data structures and algorithms.
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science): The paper discusses the satisfiability of linear k-CNF formulas, which falls under the scope of logic in computer science.
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The paper discusses the satisfiability of CNF formulas, which is a topic of interest in artificial intelligence.
- cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics): The paper discusses the structure and complexity of CNF formulas, which falls under the scope of discrete mathematics.
